      <h1 class='title'>Tonnage Tax (Post-Implementation Review)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c12WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_12ws' title='Col. 12WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 July 2004 vol 424 c12WS' name='column_12ws' href='#column_12ws' rel='bookmark'>12WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-dawn-primarolo' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040720_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Ms Dawn Primarolo' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-dawn-primarolo" title="Ms Dawn Primarolo">The Paymaster General (Dawn Primarolo)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The tonnage tax was introduced in 2000 as part of a package of measures to revive the UK shipping industry. In July 2002, I announced that the Inland Revenue and the Department for Transport would commence a review of the way the regime is operating, and invited public contributions. A number of representations have been received. Individuals and groups wishing to make further representations are invited to do so by 30 September 2004. Details about how representations can be made are available on the Inland Revenue's website.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
